<p>But what should be returned? Well, whenever we edit or create a resource, we return the
resource that we just edited or created. In this context, the <code>tagline</code> <em>is</em> its own
resource... even though it's just a string. So instead of expecting JSON, let's look
for the literal text: <code>$this-&gt;assertEquals()</code> that <code>New Tag Line</code> is equal to the
string representation of <code>$response-&gt;getBody()</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="53a5e5f8c5">
