</p>
<p>But you don't <em>need</em> to do it this way: you might say:</p>
<blockquote><p>Look, we all know that you're <em>really</em> editing the <code>UnitTester</code> programmer
  resource, so I'm going to return that.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>And that's fine! This is an interesting <em>option</em> for how to think about things.
Just as long as you don't spend your days dreaming philosophically about your API,
you'll be fine. Make a decision and feel good about it. In fact, that's good life
advice.</p>
<h2 id="adding-the-string-resource-endpoint">Adding the String Resource Endpoint <a class="headerlink" href="weird-tagline-endpoint#adding-the-string-resource-endpoint" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
